OL,3,CBayeux Tapestry: What is it and why is
OL,4,Cit coming to the UK now?
OL,6,FThe Bayeux Tapestry is a 70-metre
OL,7,Flinen artifact with embroidered images
OL,8,Fdepicting the Norman Conquest of
OL,9,FEngland.
OL,11,FThe tapestry starts in 1064, and
OL,12,Ffollows the events leading up to the
OL,13,FBattle of Hastings in 1066, which saw
OL,14,FWilliam the Conqueror take the English
OL,15,Fthrone from Saxon King Harold and
OL,16,Fbecome the first Norman king of
OL,17,FEngland.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
