OL,3,CBayeux Tapestry: What is it and why is
OL,4,Cit coming to the UK now?
OL,6,FFamously, King Harold was killed
OL,7,Fduring the battle, a moment depicted
OL,8,Fin the tapestry with an arrow through
OL,9,Fhis eye.
OL,11,FThe artwork is thought to have been
OL,12,Fcommissioned around 960 years ago by
OL,13,Fthe half-brother of William the
OL,14,FConqueror. While nobody knows who made
OL,15,Fthe tapestry, many historians agree it
OL,16,Fwas likely stitched in England because
OL,17,Fof the type of needlecraft stitching
OL,18,Fand some Anglo-Saxon spelling.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
